pr_review_comment_body:
It doesn't change the logic.

It just moves where we do the work to `post_config_hook()`

```
self.time_periods = {}
for unit, second in zip(t, s):
    if self.py3.format_contains(self.format, unit):
        self.time_periods[unit] = seconds
```

`from_path_stats` returns a `Future`, so no need to spawn it onto a pool: can:
```
stats
  .and_then(move |_| {
    fs::Snapshot::from_path_stats(
      ..
    )
  })
  .map_err(...)
```

- type: REGISTRY
